designInfo.interventionModelDescription: A parallel-arm, cluster-randomised study design was selected. The unit of randomisation for the cluster-randomised trial was the traditional healer. Healers were randomly assigned (1:1) to the study intervention or control group, stratified by healer specialty (bonesetter, birth attendant, herbalist, and spiritualist).

maskingInfo.maskingDescription: Blinding of participants and study staff was not possible due to the nature of the study intervention.
